						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Pillar in the western entrance into the Yellamma temple on the Yellamma hill near Saundatti.</hi></p>						

						<p>Kṛishṇarāya—A.D. 1514-15.</p>						

						<p>This record is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1436, Bhāva,</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1514-15.</hi></p>						

						<p>The inscription states that the work of the upper storey of the stone <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> of the western gate was completed on the specified date.</p>						

